title: Scene01_Dialogue
---
Narrator: The man wakes in a brass-framed hospital bed, the air heavy with antiseptic, coal smoke, and steam. Copper pipes hiss overhead, and beyond the frosted windows, the city groans with iron wheels and distant factory bells.

Doctor: Easy, my lord. Do not rise too quickly.

Edmund: Where am I?

Doctor: Saint Bartholomew's Infirmary. There was an accident on the eastern rail line this morning. Your carriage was found overturned near the ironworks.

Edmund: The ironworks...? I was on my way to the Registry.

Doctor: So we were told.

Edmund: How long have I been here?

Doctor: You were brought in at first light.

Edmund: Then send word to House Ashworth. My family must be worried.

Doctor: Do not trouble yourself, my lord. A message has already been dispatched.

Edmund: Good. Then I am going home.

Doctor: One moment, my lord. A formality.

Narrator: He produces a brass-stamped card.

Doctor: Does your family hold a Continuance policy with any licensed house?

Edmund: My family holds one. Every house of standing does. Why do you ask?

Doctor: When a man of standing survives an accident, we are required to confirm that only one of him did.

Edmund: That is an absurd question.

Doctor: It is the law’s question, my lord. Not mine.

Narrator: A pause. The doctor sets down the card.

Doctor: My lord, I strongly advise against-

Edmund: I said I am going home.
===
